However, we can always work to strengthen our joint provisions to protect human rights and individuals from discrimination.
By remembering the grim past that the European Union has grown from it can help guide us in the most appropriate direction for the future.
Â Â  The real subject of the resolution I have voted in favour of is not only Auschwitz but also Dachau, Mathausen and those 23 concentration camps that give chilling and resounding echo to the nature of mankind, characterised as we are by oceans of darkness, as well as of light.
